<subSubSection id="A1946504FFF0FF91DC4CF7F6F9D4400B" pageId="31" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91DC4CF7F6FD424C93" blockId="31.[307,1176,2031,2762]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">DESCRIPTION.—Form: Short and broad, highly convex, and with a small depressed head. Easily distinguished from the other species of the group by the well-developed laterobasal carinae of the pronotum and the deep triangular fova formed medial to the carina.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91DC48F603FE3D4F1F" blockId="31.[307,1176,2031,2762]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91DC48F603FE134CA3" box="[349,459,2445,2481]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Color:</emphasis>
Piceous, very shiny; appendages testaceous; antennal articles apically and femora slightly infuscated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91DC4EF599FB404FD7" blockId="31.[307,1176,2031,2762]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91DC4EF599FE1F4F29" box="[347,455,2583,2619]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Head:</emphasis>
Narrow between eyes; frontal furrows short, arcuate, ended at anterior supraorbital setigerous pore; frons with two deeply impressed fovae each side of midline; eyes depressed, medium-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91D9C7FE6BF99C4718" blockId="31.[1233,2129,485,1677]" box="[1234,1604,485,522]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<heading id="B27981E3FFF0FF91D9C7FE6BF99C4718" bold="true" box="[1234,1604,485,522]" fontSize="11" level="9" pageId="31" pageNumber="28" reason="6">sized, and prominent.</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91D9E2FD9AF91E460F" blockId="31.[1233,2129,485,1677]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D9E2FD9AFA44472A" box="[1271,1436,532,568]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Pronotum</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71B52A0AFFF0FF91D8CDFD9DF944472A" box="[1496,1692,531,568]" captionStart="FIGURES 52, 53" captionStartId="31.[1244,1347,2657,2687]" captionTargetBox="[1238,2063,1829,2625]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 52, 53.—Pronotum, dorsal aspect: 52, Xystosomus inflatus, male, Caraca, Brazil; 53, X. convexus, female, Minas, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6023362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6023362/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Figure 52</figureCitation>
): Broadly transverse (W/L, 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D844FDCFFABE4774" bold="true" box="[1361,1382,577,614]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">x</emphasis>
1.74; range 1.72-1.83; 7 specimens); lateral setigerous pores present just anterior to middle and at hind angles; laterobasal carinae well developed; hind angles obtuse, sides anterior to angles slightly arcuate; side margins beaded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91D9ECFCA8F7F346C6" blockId="31.[1233,2129,485,1677]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D9ECFCA8FAB54658" box="[1273,1389,806,842]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Elytra:</emphasis>
Smooth, side margins narrowly reflexed; humeral projection absent, humerus evenly rounded or slightly concave posteriorly; chaetotaxy as in 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D825FC21FA1246C1" box="[1328,1482,943,980]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName id="2E8E4D0CFFF0FF91D825FC21FA6746C1" authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1973" box="[1328,1471,943,980]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">X laevis</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
plica very 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91DB91FC21F90346C6" box="[1668,1755,943,980]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">small</emphasis>
, evident externally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91D9E3FC51F8684123" blockId="31.[1233,2129,485,1677]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D9E3FC51F9DA4111" box="[1270,1538,991,1027]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Microsculpture:</emphasis>
Frons with transversely stretched meshes; absent from pronotum and elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91D9EFFBB5F96541A9" blockId="31.[1233,2129,485,1677]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D9EFFBB5F9F9414D" box="[1274,1569,1083,1119]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Secondary sexual</emphasis>
characters: 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91DBEBFBB4F834414D" box="[1790,2028,1082,1119]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D505FBB4F789414D" box="[2064,2129,1082,1119]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Figure</emphasis>
54) and female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="71B52A0AFFF0FF91DBE7FBE6F842419F" box="[1778,1946,1128,1165]" captionStart="FIGURE 55" captionStartId="32.[304,395,2702,2732]" captionTargetBox="[320,1121,1853,2675]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 55.—Female genitalia, ventral aspect, with spermathecal reservoir, of Xystosomus inflatus, Nova Friburgo, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828576/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Figure 55</figureCitation>
) characteristic of the 
<taxonomicName id="2E8E4D0CFFF0FF91D8DCFB18F99D41A8" authorityName="Schaum" authorityYear="1859" box="[1481,1605,1174,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D8DCFB18F99D41A8" box="[1481,1605,1174,1210]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFF0FF91D9ECFB48F9D4400B" blockId="31.[1233,2129,485,1677]" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFF0FF91D9ECFB48FA9141F8" box="[1273,1353,1222,1258]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="28">Size:</emphasis>
Eight specimens: length, 2.4—2.9 mm; width, 1.3-1.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
